## Design Decisions Locked In

Based on resolving the above questions, here are the final design decisions to update in the main blueprint:

1. **NMT is a platform equity token** (not a direct land value peg) — its floor rises via revenue
2. **Three-token architecture**: NMT (platform) + sNFT (title) + pSHARE (fractional ownership)
3. **Floor is a one-way ratchet** — once a new floor is set, it is permanent (enforced by contract)
4. **Burns increase the floor** — they shrink the denominator, raising the price per token
5. **Cold start via seed round + grants** — treasury starts small and grows with the platform
6. **Treasury reserve holds a basket** (USDC + ETH, later nUSD) for resilience
7. **Six-layer security model**: Audits + Timelock + Multisig + Floor enforcement + DAO upgrade control + Insurance
8. **Protocol is decentralized; company is not** — they co-exist (this is standard for DeFi protocols)
9. **Protocol-first, credibly neutral design** — no admin key, open standards, other apps and DeFi protocols can plug in freely
10. **Gradual decentralization path** — company leads at launch, progressively hands control to NMT DAO over 3 years
11. **Nomentral becomes land infrastructure, not just a land app** — any government, fintech, or DeFi protocol can integrate sNFTs

